INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(43323, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A moment to reminisce on how far we have come. A day to look to the future and where we might go. A year of reflection on what it means to grow and a lifetime of memories made by those brave enough to seize it.', 57689), -- A Time to Reflect
(84616, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is fulfilling to see so many denizens of Azeroth and beyond visiting our celebration. It is in remembering all our pasts that we are able to come together and celebrate. \n\nWe hope that you will continue to enjoy our event. To assist you in your own adventures, take this boon of the bronze flight!', 57689), -- Celebrate Good Fun!
(84726, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Curious. Even as fragments, the pieces hum with energy. I wonder if I...\n\n<Angorla presses the fragments together like a puzzle, squeezing them in her palm. After a moment, she opens her hand and reveals a neatly-fused shard.>\n\nIt may be less intricately-carved or ornate as the citrine you found in the vault, but there is power here, even in a small stone like this.', 58162), -- Uncovered Mysteries
(84241, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well fought. Your assistance was most welcome, $n. The Sacred Flame guided our hand and steel.\n\n\nBut now I have the situation under control. Perhaps a few of the goblins or earthen who yet remain may need your aid?', 58187), -- Shoreline Stand
(84225, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew you\'d take care of thay creepy mess!', 58187), -- Eggstinction
(86486, 7, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The snapdragon barely waits for you to drop the rations before voraciously devouring them. Clearly it was hungry.\n\nOnce it finishes, it looks contented and drowsy. You realize it won\'t be this way for long. Perhaps you should try to feed it again tomorrow.>', 58238), -- Hungry, Hungry Snapdragon
(86482, 432, 418, 377, 12, 0, 2, 5, 8, '<The small snapdragon voraciously tears into the morsel. It seems to be energized by both the meat and the caffeinated Kaja\'Cola the meat was soaked in.\n\nIt looks up at you with gratitude in its eyes. \n\nIt will remember you.>', 58187), -- A Lifeline
(86556, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, $n, you have returned. An otherworldly air hangs heavy about you.', 58238), -- A Shattered Journey Through Time
(83274, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it, $n! Way to show those old warriors that Azeroth is still in good hands!', 57689), -- An Original Path Through Time
(82783, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks so much for the help!\n\nI\'m so excited for my first tour. It\'s MUCH more likely that no one will die or get lost now, thanks to you. Not that it has happened... ever...', 57212), -- Chromie's Codex
(84489, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope you found something to your liking, or at the very least had fun browsing.\n\nYou know your way around, so now I turn you loose to go forth and enjoy yourself. This anniversary is for you, after all.', 57171), -- Shopping Squee!
(84254, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I trust you found that we offer something of interest to you while you celebrate with us.\n\nAs promised, here is your gift.\n\n<Yllana hands you a small festive bag with a notable heft to its contents. Whatever is inside feels expensive.>', 57171), -- Meet and Greet
(82672, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome! \n\nIt\'s that special time of year when the bronze dragonflight celebrates all that has happened over the years.\n\nYou, $n, are a most honored guest!', 57171), -- Another Timely Invitation
(85573, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. I\'m glad that\'s done... I hope he can rest in peace now with his friends and crew.\n\nI did manage to transcribe a copy of the journal if you\'re interested in reading it. I thought it might come in handy.\n\n<Stellin pauses, looking thoughtful.>\n\nI wonder though... what happened to the crew? Why did the author end up alone?\n\nIt seems this island still has many mysteries to unravel.', 58187), -- Laid To Rest At Last
(85572, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh! $p I\'m glad you\'re here. I\'ve had a breakthrough with the journal, but first I want to know what you\'ve found.\n\nDid you find anything interesting? Was anyone able to decipher the handwriting?', 58187), -- A Group Effort
(85571, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wow, look at all these pages! \n\nExcellent work $p! Now, for the hardest part...', 58187), -- Scattered To The Winds
(84252, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for helping out Benny. You can borrow the Go-Pack anytime ya want!', 58187), -- Peak Precision
(85570, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, hello $p! What have you got there?', 58187), -- The Tattered Journal
(85876, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fascinating. This \"galeorn\" you spoke of known as Thrayir may be worth further investigation.\n\nPerhaps we could uncover more about its significance along with those runekeys.\n\nIt seems my curiosity will not be terminated any time soon.', 58187), -- Reading the Runes
(84248, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was a close call. We must stay alert and watch for other strange activities.', 58187), -- A Ritual of Runes
(86484, 7, 377, 0, 0, 0, 3, 0, 0, '<Upon seeing the meat you have brought it, the snapdragon clicks its jaw hungrily. The second you set down the meat it tears into it veraciously finishing the meal in seconds.\n\nIt looks up at you with newfound respect in it\'s eyes; after all, you have slain mighty creatures to bring it this meal.>', 58238), -- Temper Like A Tempest
(86483, 7, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The snapdragon perks up as you approach and sniffs the air as if to check to see if you\'ve brought it food. \n\nThe second it sees the rations in your hand it begins snapping it\'s jaws in anticipation of a tasty meal. \n\nWith a newly full belly the snapdragon runt lays down to rest but peers up at you, as if hoping you will return tomorrow.>', 58238), -- Snap To It
(84701, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Have ye come tae say goodbye?', 58162), -- The Speaker
(82702, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve brought me far more than just information. \n\nAlthough I have a feeling that this... Orweyna... will not give up her secrets easily. I should be patient. I am sure that we will find common ground eventually.\n\nIn the meantime, there is someone that she should talk to.', 58162), -- Found Friends
(82701, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'After I escaped from that place, I saw you battling the gigantic machine, and I had to join in the fight.\n\nNow it seems there really is no going back. I am alone here, except for you, and these goblins.', 58162), -- Bat Versus World
(82700, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It would seem that we are all searching for information, but I have some that I think is useful.\n\nAnd it\'s too late to hide now, they\'ve seen my true form. \n\nLet\'s see this through to the end.', 58162), -- Built to Blast
(82698, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like you\'re interested in the foreman\'s office too, huh?\n\nDon\'t get cranky, we\'re on the same side here. I just can\'t get close without being seen. \n\nAnd then there\'s just one big, clanking wrinkle to this whole mess.', 58162), -- Haywired and Hostile
(82699, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those goblins only know part of the story. What\'s in there is the full story, or at least, a big piece that\'s missing.', 58162), -- Hey, What's Going On?
(82697, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect. Now anytime someone asks why we\'re here, we\'ve got this. Now it\'s time to do a little snooping.\n\n... There are a lot more goblins here than I remember. Something\'s definitely going on.', 58162), -- Good Help These Days
(82696, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There seem to be goblins everywhere now. \n\nDo not look too closely at me, or you will draw attention. We need to get closer to where the goblins are working.', 58162), -- Ringing in the Deeps
(82695, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I understand.\n\nWe must go to where I can hear the sounds of things moving beneath the stones. I don\'t know what it means, I only know that I must go there.\n\nWill you go with me?', 58162), -- The Voice
(82694, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Na\'layro. Kai\'shae. Ney\'leia. On\'hiea.\n\nHannan.\n\nWe were a family all on our own, here, far away from home. \n\nI do not blame them for wanting to return, but I would blame myself if I gave up now. I must focus on what comes next.', 58162), -- Together, Alone
(82691, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should give us some space to retreat.\n\nAnd now we must deal with the crux of the issue. That is, Orweyna\'s ever-lasting determination to pursue this mission, no matter the cost.\n\nIt\'s time we had a talk.', 58162), -- No Breathing Room
(82692, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Orweyna counts the number of haranir silently-- to reassure herself. Then she nods.>\n\nThat\'s all of us. And I\'m grateful. \n\nThose flowers you found are also odd. They seem to have corrupted properties and have become something new. I have to dig into this more.\n\nWe can\'t stop now. Not when we\'re so close. This could be the key to how we fight back.', 58162), -- Price of a Mission
(82693, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Orweyna nods.>\n\nThank you.', 58162), -- Standing in the Way
(82690, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I didn\'t expect to see you here.\n\nBut then, you always manage to show up where there\'s something interesting, don\'t you? \n\nThere is no time for talk, though. My people have run into problems.', 58162), -- Lingering Shadows
(83277, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see you\'ve returned my Spindle to me. And some rather interesting bits of evidence, to boot.\n\nIt seems that varlet Meesk has leveraged a willingness to slander his betters in order to gain the favor of Ansurek and her ilk. Not only is his power growing by the day, but it does so at the expense of Queen Neferess\' legacy.\n\nWell, that simply will not stand. Return to me soon, my little morsel. I need some time to concoct our next course of action.', 58162), -- Personal Pilfering
(83276, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The little spider looks at you with many pleading eyes. You get the sense that she does not want you to speak of this to anyone.>', 58162), -- Saving Private Spindle
(40787, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, another one of these pesky artifacts. The meddling in the timestreams has grown worse of late... or is it that it will grow worse?$b$b<She sighs heavily.>', 58238), -- The Smoldering Ember
(83285, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Scrolls are fascinating items. They travel far and wide across the lands, yet this one seems to also travel through time.\n\nThe fact that you found this scroll where you did is both an omen and a blessing.', 57689), -- The Ancient Scroll
(80685, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A small tag on this present reads:$b$bHappy holidays, $n!', 58238), -- A Winter Veil Gift
(80684, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This present looks like it has been shaken a few times. The tag on it reads:$b$bTo a very special $r $c.', 58238), -- A Gently Shaken Gift
(81560, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, ho hello there! You can only be here for one reason: to open your Winter Veil presents.$b$bNow, don\'t you worry, Greatfather Winter hasn\'t forgotten about his favorite $r $c. Look under the tree and you\'ll find your gifts.$b$bDuring this season of giving, perhaps your friends would also enjoy receiving some of Smokywood Pasture\'s excellent products?', 58238), -- Winter's Presents
(82679, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'More o\' them! I wonder what we\'ll discover this time!', 58238), -- Archives: Seeking History
(84725, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can feel it from here... radiating. Thrumming with a long-dormant power.\n\nWho carved these small little citrines? Why do they appear to fit perfectly into the Circlet yet... they were found separated?\n\nOh, how I wish I had seen what you and Bargus had found within the Vault...', 58162), -- The Circlet Calls
(84728, 1005, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Angorla holds the glowing citrine in her hand before holding it out to you.>\n\nThat seemed to do the trick... I\'ve never felt such energy radiate from such a small crystal before. \n\nThe runes engraved on it are quite ancient and very powerful.', 58162), -- Reforged Anew
(84724, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'More queries and very few answers.\n\nFortunately, the device was able to gather some data from the energy readings. \n\nIt will take time to process, but we will soon have a better understanding of this \"Siren Crystal.\"\n\nIn the meantime, let\'s take a closer look at that ring and citrine shard you found. Angorla here will be able to help.', 58162), -- The Radiant Vault
(84723, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By the forge... this is...\n\n<Bargus stares wide-eyed in wonder at the gleaming crystal, struggling to find words. After a moment, he nods.>\n\nThis is most certainly the source of the second signature, though the energies here appear to have fused with the original.\n\nIt\'s almost like it wanted us to find this place...', 58162), -- Buried Secrets
(84941, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Bargus looks around the crumbled ruins in the cave.>\n\nThe crystals on that tablet...\n\nIf those small crystals are the source of the new energy signature, then why do they give off a stronger reading than the larger facet on the surface?\n\nThere is something else here we are missing...', 58162), -- Cave Barging
(84727, 274, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It would seem we are not alone on this island after all, $n.\n\n<Bargus glances down at the dead vrykul next to him and shakes his head with a frown.>\n\nTo initiate violence before diplomatic engagement... An illogical provocation that yielded unfortunate consequences.', 58162), -- The Second Signal
(84722, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fascinating!\n\nThe pylons\' attunement indicates this crystal is far larger than this facet would suggest. \n\nAccording to the complexity of the signature, it appears to stretch for miles beneath our feet and--wait, what is this?\n\nA second signature appears to be originating from over the hill? Curious indeed...', 58162), -- Facet-nating Signals
(84721, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Skepticism... disengaged. \n\nIt would seem the radiant remnants from Hallowfall harmonize perfectly with the energies found here, giving us a proper signature to latch onto.\n\nThe goblins\' batteries are... more than we need, but they appear to be doing the job effectively.\n\nWe\'re almost ready for the field test!', 58162), -- To Scan a Crystal
(84940, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Bargus looks up from his anvil.>\n\nAnother new arrival. \n\nHere to lend a hand to our efforts?', 58162), -- Friendly Competition
(84720, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We made it safe and sound!\n\nRicket says the whole camp\'s still buzzin\' about the crystal.\n\nSeems like everyone\'s got different ideas on how to go about figurin\' out what to do with it.\n\nThey didn\'t like Ricket and I\'s way but, you might be better at diplomacy.\n\nYou wanna get involved?', 58162), -- To the Siren Isle!
(84719, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, so you\'re the one Dawn convinced to join us, eh? \n\nWell, hurry up! They\'ve been adamant about getting us a proper Stormrider-ranger-whatever escort out of the city, but it\'s takin\' too long!\n\nThe Arathi and other earthen are already on the Isle and Ricket is probably wonderin\' where the heck we are!\n\nC\'mon! I can give you the deets on the way!', 58162), -- The Expedition Awaits
(85654, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see there\'s still some people that love chaos as much as I do. <Didi wipes a small tear from her eye.>', 58238), -- Juicing Up and Storming Out
(84619, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What a fascinating collection of writings! I daresay I shall be up all night reading these.', 58238), -- Ooker Dooker Literature Club
(83753, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Couldn\'t have done better myself. Youse should have a Kaja\'Cola to celebrate.', 58238), -- Cannon Karma
(84299, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice and efficient! I knew I could count on you to keep our profit margins lookin\' good.', 58238), -- Pirate Plunder
(84001, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $n. I knew you would find a way to solve this problem.', 58238), -- Cart Blanche
(83827, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellently executed, $n. No soul should succumb to such dreadful creatures again.', 58238), -- Silence the Song
(85653, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Apprentice Tanmar takes the three Singing Fragments and looks at them dubiously.>\n\nYou can tell there is power here. I... hope I can fuse them safely. Here goes nothing. Or everything. Heh.\n\n<Apprentice Tanmar takes out a vial of viscous, golden liquid and begins piecing them together. The liquid flashes with light, and the citrine is whole again. He hands you the repaired citrine.>\n\nImpressed? Don\'t be. It was fancy glue, to be honest. But hopefully this ring\'ll further our knowledge of the isle!', 58238), -- Dipping a Toe
(85589, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 600, 0, 0, 'A little nibbled and chewed, but I can still make out the writing on these pages. Great work, $p!', 58238), -- Ruffled Pages
(84430, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'May Beledar\'s kin prosper now.', 58238), -- Crystal Crusade
(84627, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $n. I could use someone of your caliber aboard my ship--should you ever be looking for work.', 58238), -- Three Heads of the Deep
(85051, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A strange gnome he may be, but his desire to locate, salvage, and re-purpose old items is quite commendable.', 58238), -- Beach Comber
(83932, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve gathered so much valuable information. There were so many secrets to be uncovered here! \n\nI can\'t wait to start writing this book.\n\nBut I need to come up with the perfect title first...', 58162), -- Historical Documents
(85716, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is amazing! I can learn so much studying these runes up close.', 58162), -- Rune-Seared Spear
(84222, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 600, 0, 0, 'Fine work, $n. I could use someone like you in my crew. It\'s a shame you weren\'t born Arathi.', 58162), -- Secure the Perimeter
(84680, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well harnessing the elementals, $n. I eagerly await further displays of your abilities.', 58162), -- Rock 'n Stone Revival
(84432, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am not one to promote violence as a solution, but sometimes force is the only option.', 58162), -- Longship Landing
(86156, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dat was pretty easy. We should do more!', 58162), -- Getting Involved
(85059, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Jack know you could pick winner!', 58162), -- A Piece of the Action
(84424, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Time to catch you up, $n!', 57212); -- Forward, to Adventure!
